$ simple.dis
$ Mathijs Saey
$ A simple DIS Example

CHUNCK 0
$ Instructions without a matcher

$ Program entry and exit point
INST 0 0 2 $ Program entry point, a special sink
INST 1 0 1 $ Program exit  point, a special sink

$ "main function"
INST 2 1 [0 4] [0 3] $ A call to a function.
INST 3 0             $ A sink that leads to the program exit point.

DEST [0 0 0] [0 2 0] $ Accept input from entry point
DEST [0 0 1] [0 2 1] $ Accept input from entry point
DEST [0 3 0] [0 1 0] $ Send return value to program exit

$ function
INST 4 0 $ Entry sink of the function
INST 5 2 $ Function return 

DEST [0 4 0] [1 0 0] $ Send input to operation
DEST [0 4 1] [1 0 1] $ Send input to operation
DEST [1 0 0] [0 5 0] $ Send output to return

CHUNCK 1
$ Instructions that need the matcher
INST 0 3 1 { _ | 1 }